ure both are accepted.\n- **Retrospective mismatch** — The `epic-8-retrospective.md` file describes a *different* epic 8 (the old onboarding hardening epic from the v1 epics). The current sprint uses `epics-v2.md` which redefines epic 8 as \"Issue Tracking & Retro Integration\". No workaround needed — just used the v2 definition.\n- **No existing issue command to pattern-match** — The CLI has no subcommand-style commands to reference. Used Commander's `.command()` chaining pattern which is standard but untested in this codebase. The dev agent should verify Commander subcommand support works with the existing program setup.\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 14\n- By tool: Read: 7, Grep: 5, Glob: 4, Bash: 1, Write: 1, other: 0\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): `ls | grep -i issue` (~0 lines — empty)\n- Files read: 10 unique, 12 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: The second Glob for `_bmad-output/**/*epic*8*` returned the same single result as the first call — could have been skipped."}],"totalDurationMs":163286,"totalTokens":56838,"totalToolUseCount":32,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3796,"cache_read_input_tokens":52435,"output_tokens":606,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3796},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
