{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CMZbq8RrvXCKSwd18t2Hto","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n## Review Summary\n\n**Story:** 8-1-issue-tracker-module-cli\n**Files reviewed:** `src/lib/issue-tracker.ts`, `src/commands/issue.ts`, `src/lib/__tests__/issue-tracker.test.ts`, `src/commands/__tests__/issue.test.ts`, `src/index.ts`\n**Status:** All HIGH and MEDIUM issues fixed. Story status updated to `verifying`.\n\n### Issues found and fixed:\n\n| Sev | Issue | Fix |\n|-----|-------|-----|\n| HIGH | `createIssue` never validated priority against `VALID_PRIORITIES` — any string accepted | Added validation check that throws on invalid priority |\n| MEDIUM | `list` command had no try/catch — corrupted YAML would crash with unhandled exception | Wrapped in try/catch with proper `[FAIL]` output and exit code |\n| MEDIUM | `as unknown as Record<string, unknown>` double-cast on `Issue` objects in CLI | Simplified to single `as Record<string, unknown>` where safe (Issue is a plain object interface) |\n\n### Test results after fixes:\n- 4159 tests pass (3 new tests added), 0 failures\n- Coverage: 96.79% overall, all 163 files above 80% floor\n- `issue-tracker.ts`: 100% lines, 95.83% branches\n- `issue.ts` (command): 85.71% lines\n\n---\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found and fixed:**\n- HIGH: `createIssue` accepted arbitrary priority strings without validation against `VALID_PRIORITIES` constant\n- MEDIUM: `issue list` CLI action lacked error handling — corrupted YAML would produce unhandled exception\n- MEDIUM: Unnecessary double-cast (`as unknown as Record`) in CLI command file\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW):**\n- `closeIssue` does not guard against re-closing an already-done issue (idempotent but semantically misleading)\n- `VALID_STATUSES` is defined in `issue-tracker.ts` but never actually validated anywhere in the module — status is hardcoded to `backlog` on create and `done` on close, so it's dead code for now. It will matter when future stories add status transitions.\n- The `Issue` interface uses `string` for `priority` and `status` fields rather than union types — reduces type safety at compile time\n- `list` output format is plain text without column alignment — functional but not pretty for long titles\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- `issue.ts` command: 85.71% lines (uncovered: JSON output paths for create/close, lines 29, 77). Branch coverage 70%. These are the `--json` code paths for create and close which are harder to test through Commander parsing.\n- `issue-tracker.ts`: branch at line 110 (the `match` null check in `nextIssueId`) shows 95.83% — edge case where `match` regex fails is tested via the \"ignores non-matching ids\" test but the branch miss is in coverage instrumentation\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- None. The module follows existing patterns correctly. Registration in `index.ts` is clean. YAML output is compatible with `loadWorkItems()`.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None. All HIGH/MEDIUM issues resolved.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 22\n- By tool: Bash: 8, Read: 9, Edit: 3, Grep: 2, Glob: 2, Write: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): `npx vitest run --coverage` (~50 lines), `npx vitest run` full suite (~30 lines), `git status --porcelain` (~17 lines)\n- Files read: 12 unique, 13 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: The workflow.md read failed (file was .yaml not .md) — 1 wasted call. The issue.ts re-read was cached by the tool. Otherwise clean."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a9f8e0b6855aa6d55 (use SendMessage with to: 'a9f8e0b6855aa6d55' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 50468\ntool_uses: 38\nduration_ms: 253944</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2800a04b-8151-4215-bf66-1f43973b9365","uuid":"62b08188-b193-44c2-9073-250a886fafcb","timestamp":"2026-04-03T02:04:28.956Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /b