{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Eq1aj57Y52xDnC4TwoFEsr","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Agent Instructions\n2\t\n3\t## Build & Test\n4\t\n5\t```bash\n6\tnpm run build          # tsup → dist/\n7\tnpm run test:unit      # vitest (1650+ tests)\n8\tnpm run test:coverage  # vitest with c8 coverage\n9\tnpm test               # bats integration tests\n10\t```\n11\t\n12\t## Project Structure\n13\t\n14\tThis is both an **npm CLI** (`codeharness`) and a **Claude Code plugin** (`.claude-plugin/`).\n15\t\n16\t```\n17\tsrc/                    # TypeScript source → compiled to dist/\n18\t  commands/             # CLI commands (init, run, verify, status, etc.)\n19\t  lib/                  # Shared libraries (state, docker, verify-env, retry-state, etc.)\n20\t  templates/            # Embedded string templates (prompts, docker-compose, otel config)\n21\tcommands/               # Plugin slash commands (harness-run.md, harness-init.md, etc.)\n22\thooks/                  # Plugin hooks (session-start, pre-commit, post-write, post-test)\n23\tskills/                 # Plugin skills\n24\tknowledge/              # Plugin knowledge files\n25\ttemplates/              # Static templates (Dockerfile.verify)\n26\tralph/                  # Autonomous loop (ralph.sh + supporting scripts)\n27\t_bmad/                  # BMAD Method workflows and agents\n28\t_bmad-output/           # Sprint artifacts (stories, sprint-status.yaml, retros)\n29\tverification/           # Showboat proof documents\n30\t```\n31\t\n32\t## Key Conventions\n33\t\n34\t- All CLI output uses `[OK]`, `[FAIL]`, `[WARN]`, `[INFO]` prefixes\n35\t- All commands support `--json` for machine-readable output\n36\t- Exit codes: 0 success, 1 error, 2 invalid usage\n37\t- Templates are TypeScript string literals, not external files (except Dockerfile.verify)\n38\t- State file: `.claude/codeharness.local.md` (YAML frontmatter)\n39\t- Sprint status: `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/sprint-status.yaml`\n40\t- Retry state: `ralph/.story_retries` (strict `key=count` format)\n41\t\n42\t## Session Completion\n43\t\n44\tWhen ending a work session, you MUST:\n45\t\n46\t1. Run quality gates (if code changed) — tests, build\n47\t2. Push to remote: `git pull --rebase && git push`\n48\t3. Verify `git status` shows \"up to date with origin\"\n49\t4. Never stop before pushing — that leaves work stranded locally\n50\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_016AFZKnXsJY4RSoMVp9damw","session_id":"2800a04b-8151-4215-bf66-1f43973b9365","uuid":"ef50271e-cb9e-42af-8ac6-b334ecaad6c8","timestamp":"2026-04-03T02:08:16.431Z"}
