{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01NChqn64bfBWqcjXHqpEjfv","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# src/commands/\n2\t\n3\tCLI command implementations for the `codeharness` tool. Each file exports a `register*Command(program)` function that adds a command (or command group) to the Commander program instance. All commands are registered in `src/index.ts`.\n4\t\n5\t## Commands\n6\t\n7\t### init.ts\n8\tInitializes the harness in a project. Detects stack (Node.js/Python) and app type, installs dependencies, sets up Beads issue tracking, installs BMAD with patches, creates state file, scaffolds AGENTS.md and docs/, instruments OTLP, and starts the Docker observability stack.\n9\t- **Key deps:** `lib/stack-detect`, `lib/state`, `lib/deps`, `lib/beads`, `lib/bmad`, `lib/otlp`, `lib/docker`, `lib/templates`, `lib/stack-path`\n10\t- **Subcommands:** none (single action)\n11\t\n12\t### bridge.ts\n13\tBridges BMAD epics/stories into the Beads task store. Parses a BMAD epics markdown file, extracts stories with acceptance criteria, and imports them as Beads issues with deduplication.\n14\t- **Key deps:** `lib/bmad` (parser), `lib/beads` (issue creation), `lib/output`\n15\t- **Subcommands:** none; requires `--epics <path>`, supports `--dry-run`\n16\t\n17\t### run.ts\n18\tExecutes the autonomous coding loop. Pre-flight checks: plugin directory, state reconciliation, Docker availability (`isDockerAvailable()`), and orphan container cleanup (`cleanupContainers()`). Then reads sprint status, generates Ralph prompt, and spawns the agent driver with configurable iteration limits, timeouts, and retry counts. Pipes agent stdout/stderr through `driver.parseOutput()` into the Ink renderer.\n19\t- **Key deps:** `lib/docker` (isDockerAvailable), `modules/infra` (cleanupContainers), `modules/sprint` (readSprintStatusFromState, reconcileState, getSprintState), `lib/agents` (getDriver), `lib/ink-renderer` (startRenderer), `lib/output`\n20\t- **Exports:** `resolvePluginDir()`, `countStories` (re-export from run-helpers), `registerRunCommand(program)`\n21\t- **Subcommands:** none (single action with many options)\n22\t\n23\t### verify.ts\n24\tRuns the verification pipeline on completed work. Two modes: (1) story verification via `--story <id>` — parses acceptance criteria, checks preconditions, validates proof quality (rejects proofs with PENDING ACs), creates proof document, runs Showboat verify, updates state, closes Beads issue, moves exec-plan to completed; (2) retrospective verification via `--retro --epic <n>` — checks that `epic-N-retrospective.md` exists, marks it done in sprint-status.yaml. JSON output includes `proofQuality` metrics.\n25\t- **Key deps:** `modules/verify` (parseStoryACs, validateProofQuality, checkPreconditions, etc.), `lib/doc-health` (exec-plan completion), `lib/beads-sync` (sprint status for retro)\n26\t- **Flags:** `--story <id>` (story mode), `--retro` + `--epic <n>` (retro mode), `--json`\n27\t\n28\t### status.ts\n29\tDisplays current harness status and health. Shows version, stack, enforcement settings, Docker/observability state (mode-aware: local-shared, remote-direct, remote-routed), Beads summary, onboarding progress, session flags, coverage, and verification log. Supports `--check` for pass/fail health checks.\n30\t- **Key deps:** `lib/docker`, `lib/state`, `lib/beads`, `lib/onboard-checks`, `lib/stack-path`\n31\t- **Subcommands:** none; supports `--check-docker`, `--check`\n32\t\n33\t### onboard.ts\n34\tAlias for `audit` (FR16). Delegates all behavior to the shared `audit-action.ts` handler, ensuring identical output. Provides a deprecated `scan` subcommand that prints a warning before running audit.\n35\t- **Key deps:** `audit-action` (executeAudit), `lib/output` (warn)\n36\t- **Exports:** `registerOnboardCommand(program)`\n37\t- **Subcommands:** `scan` (deprecated, prints warning then runs audit)\n38\t\n39\t### audit-action.ts\n40\tShared audit action handler used by both `audit.ts` and `onboard.ts`. Contains the full audit execution logic: precondition checks, `runAudit()`, `--fix` handling (generateFixStories, addFixStoriesToState), and output formatting (human and JSON).\n41\t- **Key deps:** `modules/audit` (runAudit, generateFixStories, addFixStoriesToState), `modules/audit/report` (formatAuditHuman, formatAuditJson), `lib/onboard-checks` (runPreconditions), `lib/output`\n42\t- **Exports:** `executeAudit(opts: { isJson: boolean; isFix: boolean })`\n43\t\n44\t### teardown.ts\n45\tRemoves the harness from a project. Stops Docker containers (mode-aware), cleans OTLP instrumented scripts from package.json, deletes state file and .harness/ cache. Preserves _bmad/ and docs/ by default.\n46\t- **Key deps:** `lib/state`, `lib/observability`, `lib/docker`, `lib/stack-path`\n47\t- **Subcommands:** none; supports `--keep-docker`\n48\t\n49\t### state.ts\n50\tManages harness state via subcommands. Provides read/write access to the YAML frontmatter state file using dot-notation keys.\n51\t- **Key deps:** `lib/state` (read/write/get/set), `yaml` (stringify for display)\n52\t- **Subcommands:** `show`, `get <key>`, `set <key> <value>`, `reset-session`\n53\t\n54\t### sync.ts\n55\tSynchronizes Beads issue statuses with story files and sprint-status.yaml. Supports bidirectional, beads-to-files, and files-to-beads directions. Can sync a single story or all stories.\n56\t- **Key deps:** `lib/beads` (issue CRUD), `lib/beads-sync` (sync logic)\n57\t- **Subcommands:** none; supports `--direction <dir>`, `--story <key>`\n58\t\n59\t### coverage.ts\n60\tRuns tests with coverage measurement and evaluates results against targets. Detects the coverage tool (c8/coverage.py), runs or checks coverage, evaluates against project target, checks per-file coverage floors, and updates state.\n61\t- **Key deps:** `lib/coverage` (detection, execution, evaluation)\n62\t- **Subcommands:** none; supports `--check-only`, `--story <id>`, `--min-file <percent>`\n63\t\n64\t### doc-health.ts\n65\tScans documentation for freshness and quality issues. Checks whether AGENTS.md files and other docs are stale relative to their associated source code. Can scope checks to modules changed by a specific story.\n66\t- **Key deps:** `lib/doc-health` (scanning, freshness checks)\n67\t- **Subcommands:** none; supports `--story <id>`, `--fix` (placeholder)\n68\t\n69\t### stack.ts\n70\tManages the shared observability stack (Docker-based). Starts, stops, and shows status of the VictoriaMetrics/OTel Collector stack. Mode-aware: handles local-shared, remote-direct, and remote-routed configurations.\n71\t- **Key deps:** `lib/docker` (stack lifecycle), `lib/state`, `lib/stack-path`\n72\t- **Subcommands:** `start`, `stop`, `status`\n73\t\n74\t### retro-import.ts\n75\tImports retrospective action items as beads issues. Parses `epic-N-retrospective.md` for action item tables, classifies each item (harness/tool/project), derives priority, creates or deduplicates beads issues using gap-ids.\n76\t- **Key deps:** `lib/retro-parser` (parsing, classification, priority), `lib/beads` (createOrFindIssue, buildGapId), `lib/output`\n77\t- **Subcommands:** none; requires `--epic <n>`, supports `--json`\n78\t\n79\t### github-import.ts\n80\tImports GitHub issues labeled for sprint planning into beads. Queries GitHub via `gh` CLI for issues with a specified label (default: `sprint-candidate`), maps GitHub labels to beads type (bug/story/task) and priority, creates or deduplicates beads issues using gap-ids with format `[source:github:owner/repo#N]`.\n81\t- **Key deps:** `lib/github` (isGhAvailable, ghIssueSearch, getRepoFromRemote), `lib/beads` (createOrFindIssue, buildGapId), `lib/output`\n82\t- **Subcommands:** none; supports `--repo <owner/repo>`, `--label <label>`, `--json`\n83\t\n84\t### retry.ts\n85\tManages retry state for stories. Shows retry counts and flagged-story status, resets counters per-story or globally. Validates story keys against path traversal.\n86\t- **Key deps:** `lib/retry-state` (readRetries, readFlaggedStories, resetRetry), `lib/output`\n87\t- **Subcommands:** none; supports `--reset`, `--story <key>`, `--status`, `--json`\n88\t\n89\t### validate.ts\n90\tParent command for the `codeharness validate` group. Registers subcommands `schema` (from `validate-schema.ts`) and `self` (from `validate-self.ts`).\n91\t- **Key deps:** `validate-schema` (registerValidateSchemaCommand), `validate-self` (registerValidateSelfCommand)\n92\t- **Subcommands:** `schema` (validate YAML against JSON schemas), `self` (self-validation cycle)\n93\t\n94\t### validate-schema.ts\n95\tCLI subcommand: `codeharness validate schema`. Validates workflow YAML files against JSON schemas using `parseWorkflow()`. Accepts a path or directory, validates each `.yaml`/`.yml` file, and reports results.\n96\t- **Key deps:** `lib/workflow-parser` (parseWorkflow, WorkflowParseError), `lib/output`\n97\t- **Exports:** `registerValidateSchemaCommand(parent)`\n98\t\n99\t### validate-self.ts\n100\tCLI subcommand: `codeharness validate self`. Runs self-validation cycle and produces a release gate report. Initializes a validation sprint, loops through `runValidationCycle()` until no actionable ACs remain, then outputs a summary. Outputs \"RELEASE GATE: PASS -- v1.0 ready\" when all non-blocked ACs pass.\n101\t- **Key deps:** `modules/verify` (createValidationSprint, runValidationCycle, getValidationProgress, getACById), `lib/output`\n102\t- **Exports:** `registerValidateSelfCommand(parent)`\n103\t\n104\t### validate-state.ts\n105\tValidates sprint-state.json consistency against sprint-status.yaml. Thin CLI wrapper that delegates to the sprint module's `validateStateConsistency`.\n106\t- **Key deps:** `modules/sprint` (validateStateConsistency), `lib/output`\n107\t- **Subcommands:** none; supports `--state <path>`, `--sprint-status <path>`\n108\t\n109\t### timeout-report.ts\n110\tCaptures diagnostic data from a timed-out iteration. Called by ralph.sh on exit code 124 to preserve git diff, state delta, and partial stderr in a structured markdown report.\n111\t- **Key deps:** `modules/sprint` (captureTimeoutReport), `lib/output`\n112\t- **Subcommands:** none; requires `--story <key>`, `--iteration <n>`, `--duration <minutes>`, `--output-file <path>`, `--state-snapshot <path>`; supports `--json`\n113\t\n114\t### query.ts\n115\tQueries observability data (logs, metrics, traces) scoped to the current project. Automatically injects service_name filtering into LogsQL and PromQL queries. Resolves endpoints from state (local or remote).\n116\t- **Key deps:** `lib/state` (service name, endpoint resolution)\n117\t- **Subcommands:** `logs <filter>`, `metrics <promql>`, `traces`\n118\t\n119\t### progress.ts\n120\tUpdates live run progress in sprint-state.json. Used by harness-run to show real-time story/phase progress during autonomous execution.\n121\t- **Key deps:** `modules/sprint` (updateRunProgress, clearRunProgress), `lib/output`\n122\t- **Subcommands:** none; supports `--story <key>`, `--phase <phase>`, `--action <text>`, `--ac-progress <text>`, `--clear`, `--json`\n123\t\n124\t### observability-gate.ts\n125\tChecks observability coverage against targets for commit gating. Reads cached static and runtime coverage from sprint-state.json, compares against configurable targets (default: 80% static, 60% runtime). Used by the pre-commit hook to block commits below target.\n126\t- **Key deps:** `modules/observability` (checkObservabilityCoverageGate), `lib/output`\n127\t- **Subcommands:** none; supports `--json`, `--min-static <percent>`, `--min-runtime <percent>`\n128\t\n129\t### audit.ts\n130\tThin CLI wrapper that registers the `audit` command and delegates to the shared `audit-action.ts` handler. Supports `--json` and `--fix` flags.\n131\t- **Key deps:** `audit-action` (executeAudit)\n132\t- **Subcommands:** none; supports `--json`, `--fix`\n133\t\n134\t### stats.ts\n135\tAnalyzes token consumption and cost from ralph session logs. Parses JSONL log files for streaming API events, aggregates by phase (create-story, dev-story, code-review, verify, retro), story, tool, and date. Computes API-equivalent cost using Opus 4.6 pricing. Formats human-readable markdown report.\n136\t- **Key deps:** `lib/output` (info, ok, fail, jsonOutput), node:fs, commander\n137\t- **Subcommands:** none; supports `--save` (write report to cost-report.md), `--json`\n138\t\n139\t### verify-env.ts\n140\tManages the verification environment for black-box story verification. Builds a Docker image from project artifacts (no source code), prepares clean temp workspaces with only story docs, validates the environment, and cleans up.\n141\t- **Key deps:** `modules/verify` (buildVerifyImage, prepareVerifyWorkspace, checkVerifyEnv, cleanupVerifyEnv), `lib/output`\n142\t- **Subcommands:** `build` (build Docker image, supports `--json`), `prepare --story <key>` (create clean workspace), `check` (validate image/CLI/otel), `cleanup --story <key>` (remove workspace and container)\n143\t\n144\t## Adding a New Command\n145\t\n146\t1. Create `src/commands/<name>.ts` exporting `register<Name>Command(program: Command): void`\n147\t2. Register in `src/index.ts`, add tests in `src/commands/__tests__/`\n148\t3. Support `--json` output via `cmd.optsWithGlobals().json` and `jsonOutput()` from `lib/output`\n149\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_016AFZKnXsJY4RSoMVp9damw","session_id":"2800a04b-8151-4215-bf66-1f43973b9365","uuid":"caaf814c-930c-4116-855b-bbf3bb77f032","timestamp":"2026-04-03T02:09:02.700Z"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01LJuvPCu9DWeqmuiw2bAYTz","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# src/lib — Shared Libraries\n2\t\n3\tPure library modules consumed by CLI commands (`src/commands/`) and by each other. No CLI entry points, no side effects on import.\n4\t\n5\t## State & Output\n6\t\n7\t| File | Purpose | Key Exports |\n8\t|------|---------|-------------|\n9\t| state.ts | YAML front-matter state persistence in `.claude/codeharness.local.md` | `readState`, `writeState`, `readStateWithBody`, `getStatePath`, `HarnessState` |\n10\t| workflow-state.ts | Workflow execution state persistence in `.codeharness/workflow-state.yaml` — tracks task checkpoints, evaluator scores, circuit breaker | `readWorkflowState`, `writeWorkflowState`, `getDefaultWorkflowState`, `WorkflowState`, `TaskCheckpoint`, `EvaluatorScore`, `CircuitBreakerState` |\n11\t| output.ts | Structured `[OK]/[FAIL]/[WARN]/[INFO]` CLI output with JSON mode | `ok`, `fail`, `warn`, `info`, `jsonOutput` |\n12\t\n13\t## Stack Provider System\n14\t\n15\t| File | Purpose | Key Exports |\n16\t|------|---------|-------------|\n17\t| stacks/types.ts | Canonical stack type definitions and `StackProvider` interface | `StackProvider`, `StackName`, `AppType`, `CoverageToolName`, `CoverageToolInfo`, `OtlpResult`, `TestCounts` |\n18\t| stacks/registry.ts | Provider registry with marker-based stack detection | `registerProvider`, `getStackProvider`, `detectStacks`, `detectStack`, `StackDetection`, `_resetRegistry` |\n19\t| stacks/nodejs.ts | Full NodejsProvider — all Node.js-specific logic extracted from consumer files | `NodejsProvider` |\n20\t| stacks/python.ts | Full PythonProvider — all Python-specific logic (app type detection, coverage, OTLP, Dockerfile, pytest parsing) | `PythonProvider` |\n21\t| stacks/rust.ts | Full RustProvider — Cargo.toml parsing, tarpaulin coverage, OTLP packages, multi-stage Dockerfile, workspace test aggregation | `RustProvider` |\n22\t| stacks/utils.ts | Shared helpers for stack providers — JSON/text file reading, Node.js/Python/Cargo dependency extraction | `readJsonSafe`, `readTextSafe`, `getNodeDeps`, `getPythonDepsContent`, `hasPythonDep`, `getCargoDepsSection`, `hasCargoDep` |\n23\t| stacks/index.ts | Barrel re-exports + auto-registers NodejsProvider, PythonProvider, RustProvider on import | all public API from types.ts and registry.ts |\n24\t\n25\t## Stack & Environment (Legacy)\n26\t\n27\t| File | Purpose | Key Exports |\n28\t|------|---------|-------------|\n29\t| stack-detect.ts | Legacy stack detection — re-exports `StackName`, `AppType` from stacks/types.ts for backward compat | `detectStack`, `detectAppType`, `AppType` |\n30\t| stack-path.ts | XDG-compliant paths for shared observability stack | `getStackDir`, `getComposeFilePath`, `ensureStackDir` |\n31\t| templates.ts | File generation with `{{var}}` mustache-style rendering | `generateFile`, `renderTemplate` |\n32\t\n33\t## Docker (src/lib/docker/)\n34\t\n35\t| File | Purpose | Key Exports |\n36\t|------|---------|-------------|\n37\t| docker/index.ts | Barrel re-exports for docker subsystem | all public API from compose, health, cleanup |\n38\t| docker/compose.ts | Docker Compose lifecycle — start/stop shared stack, collector | `startStack`, `stopStack`, `startSharedStack`, `stopSharedStack`, `startCollectorOnly`, `stopCollectorOnly`, `isStackRunning`, `isSharedStackRunning`, `isCollectorRunning` |\n39\t| docker/health.ts | Docker health checks, availability, remote probing | `isDockerAvailable`, `isDockerComposeAvailable`, `getStackHealth`, `getCollectorHealth`, `checkRemoteEndpoint`, `DockerHealthResult` |\n40\t| docker/cleanup.ts | Container cleanup utilities | `cleanupOrphanedContainers`, `cleanupVerifyEnv` |\n41\t\n42\t## Observability / OTLP (src/lib/observability/)\n43\t\n44\t| File | Purpose | Key Exports |\n45\t|------|---------|-------------|\n46\t| observability/index.ts | Barrel re-exports for OTLP subsystem | all public API from instrument, config, backends |\n47\t| observability/instrument.ts | OTLP instrumentation — package install, script patching | `installNodeOtlp`, `installPythonOtlp`, `installRustOtlp`, `instrumentProject`, `patchNodeStartScript` |\n48\t| observability/config.ts | OTLP env var configuration for CLI/web/agent modes | `configureOtlpEnvVars`, `ensureServiceNameEnvVar`, `ensureEndpointEnvVar`, `configureCli`, `configureWeb`, `configureAgent` |\n49\t| observability/backends.ts | Observability backend interface with Victoria and ELK implementations | `ObservabilityBackend`, `VictoriaBackend`, `ElkBackend` |\n50\t\n51\t## Schema Validation & Workflow Parsing\n52\t\n53\t| File | Purpose | Key Exports |\n54\t|------|---------|-------------|\n55\t| schema-validate.ts | JSON Schema validation using ajv — workflow YAML structure validation with typed error reporting | `validateWorkflowSchema`, `validateAgainstSchema`, `ValidationResult`, `ValidationError` |\n56\t| workflow-parser.ts | Workflow YAML parser — reads file, validates against JSON schema, checks referential integrity, applies defaults, returns typed `ResolvedWorkflow` | `parseWorkflow`, `WorkflowParseError`, `ResolvedWorkflow`, `ResolvedTask`, `LoopBlock`, `FlowStep` |\n57\t\n58\t## Agent Infrastructure (Epic 4)\n59\t\n60\t| File | Purpose | Key Exports |\n61\t|------|---------|-------------|\n62\t| agent-dispatch.ts | SDK-based agent dispatching with retries, timeout, rate-limit handling | `dispatchAgent`, `DispatchOptions`, `DispatchResult`, `DispatchError`, `DispatchErrorCode` |\n63\t| agent-resolver.ts | Agent config resolution — loads embedded templates, applies patch chain, compiles subagent definitions | `resolveAgent`, `loadEmbeddedAgent`, `loadPatch`, `mergePatch`, `compileSubagentDefinition`, `ResolvedAgent`, `SubagentDefinition`, `AgentPatch`, `AgentResolveError` |\n64\t| session-manager.ts | Session boundary management — fresh/continue resolution, session ID recording and lookup | `resolveSessionId`, `recordSessionId`, `getLastSessionId`, `SessionBoundary`, `SessionLookupKey` |\n65\t| source-isolation.ts | Source isolation for black-box verification — creates isolated workspaces with dist artifacts only, no source code | `createIsolatedWorkspace`, `IsolatedWorkspace`, `IsolationOptions` |\n66\t| trace-id.ts | Trace ID generation per iteration, prompt injection formatting, state recording | `generateTraceId`, `formatTracePrompt`, `recordTraceId`, `sanitizeSegment` |\n67\t\n68\t## Workflow Execution (Epic 5)\n69\t\n70\t| File | Purpose | Key Exports |\n71\t|------|---------|-------------|\n72\t| workflow-engine.ts | Sequential flow execution orchestrator — composes all Epic 1-4 modules to execute workflow steps in order, dispatching agents per-story or per-run | `executeWorkflow`, `dispatchTask`, `loadWorkItems`, `EngineConfig`, `EngineResult`, `EngineError`, `WorkItem` |\n73\t\n74\t## Blind Evaluator (Epic 6)\n75\t\n76\t| File | Purpose | Key Exports |\n77\t|------|---------|-------------|\n78\t| evaluator.ts | Evaluator module — workspace spawn, SDK-based agent dispatch with timeout, Docker availability check | `dispatchEvaluator`, `EvaluatorOptions`, `EvaluatorResult`, `isDockerAvailable`, `buildUnknownOutput` |\n79\t| verdict-parser.ts | Evaluator verdict JSON schema validation and parsing — PASS-evidence invariant enforcement, typed error reporting | `parseVerdict`, `validateVerdict`, `VerdictParseError`, `EvaluatorVerdict`, `VerdictValidationResult` |\n80\t| circuit-breaker.ts | Score-based circuit breaker — detects evaluator score stagnation and signals halt to prevent token waste on repeated failing iterations | `evaluateProgress`, `CircuitBreakerDecision` |\n81\t\n82\t## Coverage & Testing\n83\t\n84\t| File | Purpose | Key Exports |\n85\t|------|---------|-------------|\n86\t| coverage.ts | Coverage tool detection (Vitest/c8/coverage.py/cargo-tarpaulin), execution, evaluation, per-file floors | `detectCoverageTool`, `runCoverage`, `checkOnlyCoverage`, `evaluateCoverage`, `checkPerFileCoverage`, `getTestCommand` |\n87\t\n88\t## Verification Pipeline\n89\t\n90\t| File | Purpose | Key Exports |\n91\t|------|---------|-------------|\n92\t| verify-parser.ts | Parses story ACs with type classification (ui/api/db/general) | `parseStoryACs`, `classifyAC`, `ParsedAC` |\n93\t| verify.ts | Verification orchestrator — preconditions, proof quality validation, Showboat, state | `checkPreconditions`, `validateProofQuality`, `ProofQuality`, `createProofDocument`, `runShowboatVerify`, `closeBeadsIssue`, `proofHasContent` (deprecated) |\n94\t| verify-env.ts | Black-box verification environment — Docker image build (npm pack/pip install), clean workspace prep, env check, cleanup | `buildVerifyImage`, `prepareVerifyWorkspace`, `checkVerifyEnv`, `cleanupVerifyEnv`, `computeDistHash`, `isValidStoryKey` |\n95\t| verifier-session.ts | Black-box verifier session spawner — runs `claude --print` in clean workspace, returns `Result<VerifyResult>`, copies proof back to project | `spawnVerifierSession`, `copyProofToProject` |\n96\t\n97\t## Documentation Health (src/lib/doc-health/)\n98\t\n99\t| File | Purpose | Key Exports |\n100\t|------|---------|-------------|\n101\t| doc-health/index.ts | Barrel re-exports for doc-health subsystem | all public API from scanner, staleness, report |\n102\t| doc-health/scanner.ts | Module detection and doc health scanning | `findModules`, `scanDocHealth`, `DocHealthResult`, `DocHealthReport` |\n103\t| doc-health/staleness.ts | Staleness checks, AGENTS.md completeness, story freshness | `isDocStale`, `getSourceFilesInModule`, `getMentionedFilesInAgentsMd`, `checkAgentsMdCompleteness`, `checkAgentsMdForModule`, `checkDoNotEditHeaders`, `checkStoryDocFreshness` |\n104\t| doc-health/report.ts | Doc health output formatting and exec-plan lifecycle | `formatDocHealthOutput`, `printDocHealthOutput`, `createExecPlan`, `completeExecPlan`, `getExecPlanStatus` |\n105\t| doc-health/types.ts | Shared types for doc-health subsystem | `DocHealthResult`, `ModuleDocHealth`, `SOURCE_EXTENSIONS` |\n106\t\n107\t## Retrospective Parsing & Retro-to-Sprint Pipeline\n108\t\n109\t| File | Purpose | Key Exports |\n110\t|------|---------|-------------|\n111\t| retro-parser.ts | Retro markdown parser — action item extraction, classification, priority derivation, section parsing, deduplication | `parseRetroActionItems`, `parseRetroSections`, `normalizeText`, `wordOverlap`, `isDuplicate`, `classifyFinding`, `derivePriority`, `RetroActionItem`, `RetroSectionItem`, `Classification` |\n112\t| retro-to-sprint.ts | Retro-to-sprint pipeline — processes retro action items into TD stories and backlog entries | `processRetroActionItems`, `ensureEpicTd`, `createTdStory`, `nextTdStoryNumber`, `generateSlug`, `getExistingTdTitles`, `appendToBacklogFile` |\n113\t\n114\t## GitHub CLI Integration\n115\t\n116\t| File | Purpose | Key Exports |\n117\t|------|---------|-------------|\n118\t| github.ts | `gh` CLI wrapper — issue create/search, label management, repo detection, dedup | `isGhAvailable`, `ghIssueCreate`, `ghIssueSearch`, `findExistingGhIssue`, `getRepoFromRemote`, `parseRepoFromUrl`, `ensureLabels`, `GitHubError`, `GhIssue`, `RetroIssueTarget` |\n119\t\n120\t## Beads Integration (Issue Tracking)\n121\t\n122\t| File | Purpose | Key Exports |\n123\t|------|---------|-------------|\n124\t| beads.ts | `bd` CLI wrapper — CRUD, init, hook detection, gap-id dedup | `createIssue`, `closeIssue`, `buildGapId`, `createOrFindIssue`, `BeadsError` |\n125\t\n126\t## Sync (src/lib/sync/)\n127\t\n128\t| File | Purpose | Key Exports |\n129\t|------|---------|-------------|\n130\t| sync/index.ts | Barrel re-exports for sync subsystem | all public API from beads, sprint-yaml, story-files |\n131\t| sync/beads.ts | Bidirectional sync between beads issues, story files, sprint YAML | `syncBeadsToStoryFile`, `syncStoryFileToBeads`, `syncClose`, `syncAll` |\n132\t| sync/sprint-yaml.ts | Sprint status YAML read/write and onboarding epic