agents without the field produce identical output.\n- **Risk — dual prompt paths**: Evaluator has both `EVALUATOR_PROMPT` (in evaluator.ts) and `SubagentDefinition.instructions` (from YAML). Both need anti-leniency instructions.\n- **All ACs test-provable**: Build + test + grep sufficient for verification.\n\n## Token Report — create-story\n- Total tool calls: 16\n- By tool: Read: 8, Grep: 6, Glob: 4, Bash: 1, Write: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: `ls _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/` (~9 lines)\n- Files read: 10 unique, 12 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: none\n\n### 6-3-evaluator-prompt-template — code-review (2026-04-03T00:40)\n\n- **HIGH fixed:** `buildEvaluatorPrompt()` accepted unused `agentDefinition` parameter — dead code removed\n- **MEDIUM fixed:** Verdict output path `./verdict/` lacked filename — changed to `./verdict/verdict.json`\n- **MEDIUM fixed:** No direct unit test for `buildEvaluatorPrompt()` in isolation — covered via integration assertions\n- **LOW (not fixed):** `buildUnknownOutput()` produces one finding per story file, not per AC (intentional)\n- **LOW (not fixed):** Prompt template in YAML duplicates some persona.principles — acceptable for reinforcement\n- Coverage: 96.81% overall, all 160 files above 80% floor\n\n## Token Report — code-review\n- Total tool calls: 18\n- By tool: Bash: 6, Read: 8, Edit: 6, Grep: 2, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: `npm run test:unit` (~50 lines x2), `npm run build` (~20 lines)\n- Files read: 10 unique, 10 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: none\n\n### 6-3-evaluator-prompt-template — verification (2026-04-03T00:47)\n\n- **Proof format mismatch:** First proof used `### AC #N:` (h3 with `#` prefix) — parser expects `## AC N:` (h2, no `#`). Rewrote.\n- **codeharness verify warnings:** Missing Showboat and exec-plan — non-blocking, still validates proof.\n- All 10/10 ACs passed with real evidence.\n\n## Token Report — verification\n- Total tool calls: 18\n- By tool: Bash: 12, Read: 5, Grep: 2, Write: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: `npm run test:unit` (~80 lines), `npx vitest --coverage | tail -60` (~60 lines), `npx vitest --reporter=verbose` (~30 lines)\n- Files read: 6 unique, 7 total reads\n- Redundant operations: vitest coverage run twice with different grep patterns; vitest verbose run twice for different test suites\n\n### 7-1-score-based-circuit-breaker-module — verification (2026-04-03T01:17)\n\n- **AGENTS.md stale**: `src/lib/AGENTS.md` didn't list `circuit-breaker.ts`. Added entry as workaround — doc gap from dev agent.\n- **Proof format mismatch**: First proof used `**Verdict:** PASS` format but `codeharness verify` expected `— PASS` in heading. Rewrote.\n- **Coverage visibility**: vitest coverage table truncates filenames, required multiple grep attempts.\n- **Workflow engine comment typo**: Line 619 has `/ Circuit breaker:` (missing second slash). Minor.\n- **Verification gaps**: None. All 10 ACs fully covered.\n\n## Token Report — verification\n- Total tool calls: 19\n- By tool: Bash: 12, Read: 3, Edit: 1, Grep: 3, Write: 2\n- Largest Bash outputs: `npx vitest run --reporter=verbose` (~40 lines), `ls verification/` (~136 lines), `npx vitest --coverage` (~60 lines)\n- Files read: 3 unique, 3 total reads\n- Redundant operations: 3 attempts to extract coverage (grep refinement), 2 runs of `codeharness verify`\n\n### 7-1-score-based-circuit-breaker-module — code-review (2026-04-03T01:10)\n\n- **HIGH fixed:** Integration test used mock mutation instead of testing real `evaluateProgress()` code path. Rewrote test to verify actual integration.\n- **MEDIUM fixed:** Old test comment inaccurate (\"triggered after dispatchCount>=2\"). Fixed.\n- **MEDIUM fixed:** Mock mutation was dead code, overwritten by real `evaluateProgress()`. Removed.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** Test for all-pass-with-stagnation scenario can't occur in production.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** No input validation on `EvaluatorScore` fields (trusts upstream).\n- **LOW (not fixed):** `remainingFailures` includes `unknown` as failures.\n- Coverage: 96.81% overall, circuit-breaker.ts at 100%, all files above 80%.\n\n## Token Report — code-review\n- Total tool calls: 21\n- By tool: Bash: 10, Read: 7, Edit: 2, Grep: 4, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: `npm run test:unit` (~60 lines), `git diff` (~80 lines), `npm run build` (~20 lines)\n- Files read: 7 unique, 8 total reads\n- Redundant operations: one extra grep with wrong regex pattern\n\n### 7-1-score-based-circuit-breaker-module — dev-story (2026-04-03T01:02)\n\n- **Test regressions from integration:** Three existing workflow-engine tests broke because mock evaluator returned same `passed: 1` every iteration, triggering stagnation. Fixed with `makeProgressingFailVerdict()` helper.\n- **remainingFailures is approximate:** Returns placeholder indices `[1..failCount]` not specific AC numbers — engine only stores aggregate `EvaluatorScore`.\n\n## Token Report — dev-story\n- Total tool calls: 16\n- By tool: Bash: 6, Read: 5, Edit: 5, Write: 2, Grep: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: `npm run test:unit` (~15 lines), `npm run build` (~10 lines)\n- Files read: 5 unique, 6 total reads\n- Redundant operations: none\n\n### 7-1-score-based-circuit-breaker-module — create-story (2026-04-03T00:57)\n\n**Problems encountered:**\n- `config.yaml` referenced in `workflow.yaml` does not exist at `_bmad/bmm/config.yaml`. Variables not resolvable. Proceeded without them.\n\n**Workarounds applied:**\n- Epic ACs sparse (one BDD block). Expanded to 10 discrete, testable ACs based on FR32-34 and architecture.\n- `remainingFailures` AC: `EvaluatorScore` only has aggregate counts, not per-AC findings. Documented limitation.\n\n**Risks identified:**\n- None truly untestable — all test-provable.\n- Tightened \"evaluation in <100ms\" to <5ms based on architecture patterns.\n\n**Observations:**\n- workflow-engine already checks `circuit_breaker.triggered` at line 651 but never sets it. This story closes that gap.\n- `CircuitBreakerState` interface already exists in `workflow-state.ts`.\n\n## Token Report — create-story\n- Total tool calls: 19\n- By tool: Bash: 3, Read: 10, Grep: 4, Glob: 5, Write: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: `ls implementation-artifacts` (~180 lines), `git log --oneline -10` (~10 lines)\n- Files read: 10 unique, 14 total reads\n- Redundant operations: none\n\n### 7-2-resume-after-circuit-breaker — verification (2026-04-03T05:38)\n\n- **BATS integration tests have code-127 failures** (pre-existing, unrelated to story).\n- **Proof format:** Initially 0/8 verified due to missing showboat markers. Fixed by rewriting proof.\n- **Verification gaps:** ACs 3, 4, 6 verified indirectly through unit tests and code inspection rather than end-to-end integration.\n- **Warnings:** Showboat not installed, no exec-plan — non-blocking for test-provable tier.\n\n## Token Report — verification\n- Total tool calls: 16\n- By tool: Bash: 11, Read: 2, Grep: 3, Write: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: `npm test` (~60 lines), `npx vitest run --coverage` (~40 lines)\n- Files read: 2 unique, 2 total reads\n- Redundant operations: coverage run 3 times (could reuse), npm test run twice\n\n### 7-2-resume-after-circuit-breaker — code-review (2026-04-03T05:30)\n\n- **HIGH fixed:** EvaluatorScore mock data missing `unknown` and `timestamp` fields — tests validated against invalid state shape.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** No test for `--resume` with `phase = 'executing'` (crashed mid-run scenario).\n- **LOW (not fixed):** Source code verification tests (lines 614-671) are brittle filesystem reads.\n- Coverage: 96.81% overall, all files above 80% floor, run.ts at 100%.\n\n## Token Report — code-review\n- Total tool calls: 16\n- By tool: Bash: 7, Read: 6, Edit: 3, Grep: 3, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: `npx vitest run --coverage` (~30 lines), `git diff --name-only` (~14 lines), `npm run build` (~12 lines)\n- Files read: 8 unique, 8 total reads\n- Redundant ope